h3. Issue Summary
When filtering issues by watcher in the JQL/Board Filter, the issues are being displayed in the Backlog but not on the Board.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a filter like this example: 
{code}
project = KAN AND  watcher = "<user>"
{code}
# Create a Kanban Board and enable the Backlog;
# Make sure you have some issues that are returned by the JQL and assign the saved filter to the newly created Board;
# Leave the issue unassigned and watch the issue with the user;
# The issue will only be displayed in the Backlog;

h3. Expected Results
The issue should appear on the backlog and on the board according to the filter query.

h3. Actual Results
The issue is only displayed on the backlog.

h3. Workaround
A possible workaround would be including another field to the filter query that could force the issue to be displayed on the board.

h3. Issue Summary

It is possible to update an issue's estimation by using the endpoint [rest/agile/1.0/issue/issueIdOrKey/estimation|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/software/rest/api-group-issue/#api-agile-1-0-issue-issueidorkey-estimation-put].

But, currently, if the estimation field being used by the board is out of context to the issue you are making the call towards, the error message states the following:
{code}
"errorMessages":["The field '<ISSUE_KEY>' is not editable on issue '<BOARD_NAME>' due to its issue type."]
{code}

Where *<ISSUE_KEY>'* should actually be the reference to the field that the call tried to update, and *<BOARD_NAME>* should actually be the key of the issue that you tried to update.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

* Set the estimation of the board to use *Story Points*;
* Configure the context of the *Story Points* field to not include the issue type corresponding to the issue you are going to make the call torwars;
* Perform a call like the following:
{code:json}
curl --request PUT \
  --url 'https://<jira_instance_url>.atlassian.net/rest/agile/1.0/issue/<ISSUE_KEY or 
 ISSUE_ID>/estimation?boardId=<BOARD_ID>' \
  --user '<EMAIL_ADDRESS>:<API_TOKEN>' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "value": "2"
}'
{code}

h3. Expected Results

The message will state:
{code}
"The field 'Story Points' is not editable on issue '<ISSUE_KEY>' due to its issue type."
{code}

h3. Actual Results

The error messages states:
{code}
"The field '<ISSUE_KEY>' is not editable on issue '<BOARD_NAME>' due to its issue type."
{code}

h3. Workaround

If you hit that error, check the field's context.

